<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-06T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-06T04:00:00-05:00" n="176" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11064: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-06T17:00:00+08:00">August 6, 1930—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 6—1:55 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>673. Legation’s 667, August 4, 5 p.m. Following from Commander in Chief,
                            August 4th: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“The U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Palos</hi> restates [<hi rend="italic">reports?</hi>] 2 Chinese, 1 British and 1
                                    Japanese gunboat engaged with Communists at Changsha yesterday.
                                    This morning a number of Ho Chien troops returned to southern
                                    end of city. There was some firing throughout the night. There
                                    are 300 Japanese present at northern end of city.</p>
                                <p>The Commander, Yangtze Patrol, now anchored off the Standard Oil
                                    Company, will take no part in military operations for the
                                    recapture of troops [<hi rend="italic">city?</hi>]. The U. S. S.
                                        <hi rend="italic">Guam</hi> is proceeding with stores and
                                    coal.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>